chunk_content: ● In addition, child program participants (“OVC”) 0-17 years of age and OVC 18-20 years of age P R completing secondary education or an approved economic strengthening intervention must: E V Be monitored at least quarterly, but as often as is necessary according to the child’s safety, schooling, E stability, and health status. Monitoring includes establishing contact in person, or virtually where N needed, to ensure that the case plan is progressing, and documentation of this contact is recorded in T I the case plan. O N Graduated: The point at which a household enrolled in a PEPFAR OVC Comprehensive Program is deemed to have become more resilient and is no longer in need of PEPFAR OVC project-provided services.
